documentation.text:
@dev user will submit the amount of tickets (SWAPATICKETS) and they must have sufficient amount of tickets in their wallet. 
 This will then create an entry with 4 random numbers between 0 - 9. 
 Each ticket user submits grants them one entry with 4 different and random numbers between 0 - 9.
 User can only submit the amount of tickets that is equivalent to the amount of SWAPATICKETS they have in their wallet.  
 When user submits ticket(s), SWAPATICKETS get burnt in the process.

setNonce(uint256).details: set nonce for randomize ticket generation.

setRewardRatio(uint8).details: Admin can change the reward ratio. This ratio represents how many SWAPAFY required to buy 1 SWAPATICKET

submitTicket(address,uint256).details: user will submit the amount of tickets (SWAPATICKETS) and they must have sufficient amount of tickets in their wallet.  This will then create an entry with 4 random numbers between 0 - 9.  Each ticket user submits grants them one entry with 4 different and random numbers between 0 - 9. User can only submit the amount of tickets that is equivalent to the amount of SWAPATICKETS they have in their wallet.   When user submits ticket(s), SWAPATICKETS get burnt in the process.

ticketsInCurrentRound().details: shows array of tickets that are in current round.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

updateMatchPoolAllocation(uint8,uint8,ui.details: updates the reward allocation ratio for each pool.  Ratios must add up to 1.   Example:  updateMatchPoolAllocation(0.5, 0.3, 0.15, 0.05)
